      "updated": 1775588150588,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Design Uber\n\nuber is a ride-sharing platform that connects passengers with driver who offers transportation services in personal vehicles.\nIt allows user to book rides on-demand from their smartphones, matching them with a nearby driver who will take them from their \nlocation to their destination.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Design Uber\n\nuber is a ride-sharing platform that connects passengers with driver who offers transportation services in personal vehicles.\nIt allows user to book rides on-demand from their smartphones, matching them with a nearby driver who will take them from their \nlocation to their destination.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "-HGGtQmFeLm5nYYnt7ixW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 513.8080523506743,
      "y": 4419.257843524989,
      "width": 1869.2786865234375,
      "height": 1024.9999999999998,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ae",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1056171188,
      "version": 4819,
      "versionNonce": 786148158,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775680062700,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Notes:\n\n-- Non-Function requiremnts are very important -> this what help us think in terms of deep-dive and make the system more efficient.\n    A. Identify the qualities that are unique for this system specifically.\n    B. Put them in context of the System -> this should make sense when you expand the design for optimizations.\n    C. If possible, quantify the load and edge cases.\n\n-- Entities are important to list down important aspect [Actors / system / service ] needed by the system.\n\n--  API - The main goal here is to go one-by-one in core entities to satisfy the Functional requirements \n    - No need to put any data-type -> that's ovious and don't need to be explictly mentioned.\n    - Note: \n        we haven't mentioned the userId in any API --> that is important for Security and should be handled by JWT tokens. \n        This should be put in the header not in the body. If put in the body, it would be exposed for tempering. \n\n-- HLD Design:\n    - We take the APIs and Entity and build the entire structure around it -> satisfying all the APIs that we have designed.\n    - We try to seperate the Ride booking and Matching service as 2 different Micro-service. --> Allows different team to work on it seperatly and scale independently also is a async service.\n    - Flow Explaination:\n       1. So we have the Ride [on their phone], they first request to the Ride Microservice, through the API gateway. \n          - Main function of the API gateway is to route request to the correct microservices, then balance the load among these microservices.\n          - It also perfroms the Security aspect with SSL termination, Authentication and rate limiting.\n       2. Ride Micro-service:\n          - This guy's main role is to Manage the Ride. \n          - When it gets a request from user based on source/destination -> it connects to a 3rd Party Mapping service -> that based on region and distance provides price estimation to user.\n          - it also creates a new entry in Primary DB -> that includes the rideId, estimate, source / destination.\n       3. Ride Matching Micro-service:\n          - This guy comes next -> once the user chose a fare -> they request the ride -> the request comes to this micro-service.\n          - The sole job of this is to match rider with a driver.  [1: 1].\n          - It connects to a location DB [drivers update their location here periodically] -> fetches like drivers who are available in say 5 kms radius.\n          - waits for some pre-defined time, if not increase the search radius and try again.\n          - It also sends a push notification to those drivers with ride details -> drivers can either accept/decline the ride.\n       4. Location micro-service:\n          - This is a utility micro-service which is crucial to handle location details of riders and drivers.\n          - drivers phone's location if they are available are priodically upadted to Location DB via this micro-service.\n       \n     Thus the above design, in corporate all the APIs that we have created.\n\n-- Deep-dive: [ Incorporating the non-functional requirements to make system Robust ]\n\n",
      "fontSize": 19.999999999999996,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Notes:\n\n-- Non-Function requiremnts are very important -> this what help us think in terms of deep-dive and make the system more efficient.\n    A. Identify the qualities that are unique for this system specifically.\n    B. Put them in context of the System -> this should make sense when you expand the design for optimizations.\n    C. If possible, quantify the load and edge cases.\n\n-- Entities are important to list down important aspect [Actors / system / service ] needed by the system.\n\n--  API - The main goal here is to go one-by-one in core entities to satisfy the Functional requirements \n    - No need to put any data-type -> that's ovious and don't need to be explictly mentioned.\n    - Note: \n        we haven't mentioned the userId in any API --> that is important for Security and should be handled by JWT tokens. \n        This should be put in the header not in the body. If put in the body, it would be exposed for tempering. \n\n-- HLD Design:\n    - We take the APIs and Entity and build the entire structure around it -> satisfying all the APIs that we have designed.\n    - We try to seperate the Ride booking and Matching service as 2 different Micro-service. --> Allows different team to work on it seperatly and scale independently also is a async service.\n    - Flow Explaination:\n       1. So we have the Ride [on their phone], they first request to the Ride Microservice, through the API gateway. \n          - Main function of the API gateway is to route request to the correct microservices, then balance the load among these microservices.\n          - It also perfroms the Security aspect with SSL termination, Authentication and rate limiting.\n       2. Ride Micro-service:\n          - This guy's main role is to Manage the Ride. \n          - When it gets a request from user based on source/destination -> it connects to a 3rd Party Mapping service -> that based on region and distance provides price estimation to user.\n          - it also creates a new entry in Primary DB -> that includes the rideId, estimate, source / destination.\n       3. Ride Matching Micro-service:\n          - This guy comes next -> once the user chose a fare -> they request the ride -> the request comes to this micro-service.\n          - The sole job of this is to match rider with a driver.  [1: 1].\n          - It connects to a location DB [drivers update their location here periodically] -> fetches like drivers who are available in say 5 kms radius.\n          - waits for some pre-defined time, if not increase the search radius and try again.\n          - It also sends a push notification to those drivers with ride details -> drivers can either accept/decline the ride.\n       4. Location micro-service:\n          - This is a utility micro-service which is crucial to handle location details of riders and drivers.\n          - drivers phone's location if they are available are priodically upadted to Location DB via this micro-service.\n       \n     Thus the above design, in corporate all the APIs that we have created.\n\n-- Deep-dive: [ Incorporating the non-functional requirements to make system Robust ]\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "fjEsovhJz4Jm0XF29Xwsd",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 711.8179786877731,
      "y": 910.508465375528,
      "width": 1291.43994140625,
      "height": 615.0446573893227,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aj",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 457607052,
      "version": 1735,
      "versionNonce": 1016425268,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775591492901,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Requirement Analysis\n\nFunction Requirements ( User can do requirements ):\n1. User should be able to insert start location & Destination and get price estimate.\n2. User should be able to request a ride based on estimate.\n3. Drivers should be able to Accpept/Decline request, naviagte to pickup/drop-off\n\n-- out of scope ---\n- multiple car types.\n- ratings for drivers or ride.\n- scheduling my ride prior.\n\n\nNon-Function Requirements ( Qualities of a system like \"-lities\" eg: scalability or availablity etc ) :\n1. low latency in matching < 1 min to match or failure   [ this fits w.r.t the requirement ]\n2. CAP Theorem -> We need consitency here i.e Ride to driver should be 1:1  [Each Ride must correctly matched with 1 driver.]\n3. Availablity -> It should be available outside matching ->  minimise downtime, the system should be reliable.\n4. Handle high throughout  --> Handles peak hour traffic in case of any events or office hours. 100 thousands of req in a given region.\n\n--- out of scope ---\n- GDPR user privacy  [user data protection rules]\n- Tolerance and handling system Failures\n- Monitoring, logging, alerting etc\n- CI/CD pipelines.\n",
      "fontSize": 19.681429036458326,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Requirement Analysis\n\nFunction Requirements ( User can do requirements ):\n1. User should be able to insert start location & Destination and get price estimate.\n2. User should be able to request a ride based on estimate.\n3. Drivers should be able to Accpept/Decline request, naviagte to pickup/drop-off\n\n-- out of scope ---\n- multiple car types.\n- ratings for drivers or ride.\n- scheduling my ride prior.\n\n\nNon-Function Requirements ( Qualities of a system like \"-lities\" eg: scalability or availablity etc ) :\n1. low latency in matching < 1 min to match or failure   [ this fits w.r.t the requirement ]\n2. CAP Theorem -> We need consitency here i.e Ride to driver should be 1:1  [Each Ride must correctly matched with 1 driver.]\n3. Availablity -> It should be available outside matching ->  minimise downtime, the system should be reliable.\n4. Handle high throughout  --> Handles peak hour traffic in case of any events or office hours. 100 thousands of req in a given region.\n\n--- out of scope ---\n- GDPR user privacy  [user data protection rules]\n- Tolerance and handling system Failures\n- Monitoring, logging, alerting etc\n- CI/CD pipelines.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
