      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b00",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 978343732,
      "version": 135,
      "versionNonce": 594877620,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775589782336,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Core Entities\n\n- Rider\n- Driver\n- Ride\n- location  [ will have updated location of driver ]",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Core Entities\n\n- Rider\n- Driver\n- Ride\n- location  [ will have updated location of driver ]",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "vKtla4tZAaWRNOxigPbWq",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2136.2777353176157,
      "y": 655.9351487489263,
      "width": 1499.650468744438,
      "height": 1071.8667671736212,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b07",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2023675660,
      "version": 1874,
      "versionNonce": 166978700,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775591512922,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "API\n\n1. An API to handle the fare-estimationg based on where i want to go.  POST as we going to add a new Ride entry.\n\nPost /ride/fare-estimate -> Partial<Ride>  [Returns a Ride if found with rideId, location and estimate fare]\n{\n    source,\n    destination\n}\n\n2. user should be able to request a ride to match a rider -> if he is okay with the fare estimation.  PATH as we are updating the same Ride entry\n\nPath /ride/request  -> 200 ok status   [There it might take some time to match with a driver -> so make this call async ]\n{\n     rideId,\n      \n}\n\n3. Location update of Drivers --> Drivers must call an API to update their most recent location priodically.\n\nPost /location/update\n{\n    lat,\n    long\n}\n\n4. Driver should be able to accept or decline a Ride when they are prompted with. -> Patch as we update the same ride row.\n\nPath /ride/driver/accept\n{\n    rideId,\n    true/false\n}\n\n5. Driver naviagtion to pickup and destination -> kind of driver's status of ride.\n\nPATCH /ride/driver/update -> lat,long or null\n{\n    rideId,\n    status: pickedup | droppedoff | in-transit\n}",
      "fontSize": 20.91447350582676,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "API\n\n1. An API to handle the fare-estimationg based on where i want to go.  POST as we going to add a new Ride entry.\n\nPost /ride/fare-estimate -> Partial<Ride>  [Returns a Ride if found with rideId, location and estimate fare]\n{\n    source,\n    destination\n}\n\n2. user should be able to request a ride to match a rider -> if he is okay with the fare estimation.  PATH as we are updating the same Ride entry\n\nPath /ride/request  -> 200 ok status   [There it might take some time to match with a driver -> so make this call async ]\n{\n     rideId,\n      \n}\n\n3. Location update of Drivers --> Drivers must call an API to update their most recent location priodically.\n\nPost /location/update\n{\n    lat,\n    long\n}\n\n4. Driver should be able to accept or decline a Ride when they are prompted with. -> Patch as we update the same ride row.\n\nPath /ride/driver/accept\n{\n    rideId,\n    true/false\n}\n\n5. Driver naviagtion to pickup and destination -> kind of driver's status of ride.\n\nPATCH /ride/driver/update -> lat,long or null\n{\n    rideId,\n    status: pickedup | droppedoff | in-transit\n}",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
